data.title: Principality of Saxony
data.text:
The Principality of Saxony, colloquially known as Saxony, is an independent micronation in association with Groot-Brabant. They share a common military and bank, they are in a monetary union with them and share trading and customs.

History

The Principality of Saxony is located on the southern coasts of cornwall. It was established on the 14th of august 2019 when a conflict occured to liberate the land from Fesmar.

Royal dynasty

The royal dynasty is called Chamberstar, the Chamberstar dynasty has 3 cadet branches that all lead a state in the Belgican empire namely:

The Benesek branch, the Baumans branch and the Vierstraete branch.

The Beneseks are mainly active in Cornwall with 2 brothers ruling 2 out of the 7 nations in Cornwall, John leads Penzancia and Hans leads Saxony.

The branch Baumans and Vierstraete are the two royal families of the Belgian states, the family Vierstraete is the imperial family seated in Groot-Brabant and the family baumans is seated in het kongingkrijk van De Dijle
